<br>
There are some really great offers going on now that the key rate is lower than inflation (also a strong indicator that if there is no economic recovery by March of next year that we will go from a recession to a depression).<br>
<br>
AT&amp;T is offering their credit/phone cards with 0.0% APR on all transfered balances and new purchases.  <br>
<br>
If you have a home you can refinance, but generaly speaking if you bought your house in the last 5 years your interest rate is probably pretty low already.  But if you own a home and have any outstanding debt, now would be a great time to get a line of credit and transfer your debt to your house.<br>
<br>
If anyone has any questions you can always email me at Figmentsf@yahoo.com.  I'd be happy to answer any questions.  Sorry for the mini-thread hijack haha.<br>
